<p>The post <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/catalogue/hm-0710/">HM-0710</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com">Hammar</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Control Panel 2 is a Control Unit in an Electronic Remote Release System; it is Hammar&#8217;s most advanced Control Unit, a customised solution for activation of multiple lifesaving appliances, evacuation systems or loads. The Unit is capable of handling up to 10 <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/product-category/remote-release-systems/errs/release-units-errs/">Release Units</a> (ERU) and 2 <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/product-category/remote-release-systems/errs/input-relays/">Input Sensors</a>, and another 2 ERUs + 4 Input Sensors with small modifications. A Control Panel 2 can play a centralised role in a controlled, safe and fast evacuation of a vessel.</p>
<p>CP2 is programmed on delivery based on the setup on the individual vessel and can activate ERUs individually or in a predefined sequence differentiated in time. It is a self-checking system and will not bring attention until awoken from its idle state or an error is detected.</p>
<p>The CP2 may be used to open hatches or close fire doors.</p>
<p>The HM-0710 has a rechargeable back-up battery (<a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/catalogue/hm-0725/">HM-0725</a>) in case of power failure on the ship&#8217;s 24V DC emergency power supply.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com/catalogue/hm-0710/">HM-0710</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.cmhammar.com">Hammar</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
